ication or a Key Safety role on Network Rail Managed Infrastructure will be enforced.\",\"aboutTheRole\":{\"essential\":[\"Provide advice and support to the route teams on all primarily Health and wellbeing issues. Promote a positive cultural and behavioural change in all aspects of workforce health, safety and environmental management.\",\"The role can be based in Rugby ROC or Birmingham Baskerville House.\"],\"desirable\":[\"National Examination Board in Occupational Safety & Health (NEBOSH) Certificate\",\"Knowledge of safety and compliance management processes\",\"Knowledge of relevant standards and procedures\",\"Knowledge of environmental management system\",\"Knowledge of operational railway environment\",\"Analytical capability\",\"Local Accident & Incident Investigation\",\"Knowledge of coaching techniques\",\"Good interpersonal, influencing, communication and organisation skills\",\"NEBOSH diploma\",\"A relevant professional qualification in Social Work, Counselling\",\"Membership of a relevant professional body\",\"Institute of Environmental Management Award (IEMA)\"],\"keyAccountabilities\":[\"Provide support, coaching and guidance to the route teams for issues of health and wellbeing.\",\"Providing a timely intervention provision to support managers in addressing mental wellbeing issues amongst staff\",\"Provide support to the safety and HR teams in the collation of workforce health and safety data.\",\"Monitor and analyse workforce health and safety data for trends, produce reports and make recommendations for corrective actions.\",\"Identify health, safety & wellbeing key risks and make recommendations for control measures.\",\"Support the implementation of national and local programmes and initiatives to improve workforce health, safety and wellbeing control.\",\"Facilitate the route teams in their relationships via local safety forums/groups with Trade Union Safety Representatives and external safety bodies.\",\"Provide guidance to the route teams in the investigation and reporting of accidents and incidents and the Formal Investigation Process and supporting staff  well being during the investigation\",\"Facilitate arrangements for safety and health audits.\",\"Coordinate and monitor safety tours and staff surveillance for the team.\",\"Undertake a sample check each period of local health and wellbeing plans. Take action to address issues as identified.\",\"Take an active role in developing the route teams in matters of health and wellbeing.\"]}}"